{{Infobox song contest country | Name = Albania | Flag = Flag of Albania.svg | Caption = [[Flag of Albania]] | Member station = [[Radio Televizioni Shqiptar]] (RTSH) | National selection event = Internal selection | Apps = 2 | First = {{Tscyr|2014}} | Last = {{Tscyr|2015}} | Best = 8th: {{Tscyr|2015}} | Worst = 19th: {{Tscyr|2014}}<sup>(SF)</sup> | Website = | Current TSC = 2015 }} The participation of '''Albania in the Turkvision Song Contest''' first began in [[Kazan]], [[Tatarstan]], at the second edition of the [[Turkvision Song Contest]] in 2014. [[Radio Televizioni Shqiptar]] (RTSH) have been responsible for the selection process of their participants, since their debut in 2014. Xhoi Bejko was the first representative for Albania at the [[Turkvision Song Contest 2014]] with the song "Hava ve Ates", which failed to qualify from the semifinals, finishing in nineteenth place and achieving one-hundred and fifty-four points. Albania continued to participate in the contest, and sent Xhoi Bejko and Visar Rexhepi as their representatives in the [[Turkvision Song Contest 2015]], with the song "Adi Hasret", which finished in eighth place, receiving the same total of points as in their previous participation.
==Origins of the contest== Turkvision is an annual song contest which was created by [[TÜRKSOY]] in cooperation with the Turkish music channel [[TMB TV]]. Based on the similar format of the [[Eurovision Song Contest]], Turkvision focuses primarily on participating [[Turkic peoples|Turkic]] countries and regions. The participating countries and regions have to take part in the Semi Final. A juror from each nation awards between 1 and 10 points for every entry, except their own. An amount of 12 to 15 nations qualify for the Grand Final where the jury determines the winner. TÜRKSOY has stated that televoting is going to be introduced in the future.<ref>{{cite web|title=What is Turkvision, How is the Format of Turkvision Song Contest |url=http://www.turkvision.info/What-is-Turkvision,-How-is-the-Format-of-Turkvision-Song-Contest-1-h.htm |publisher=turkvision.info |accessdate=22 April 2017 |date=15 October 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308012519/http://turkvision.info/what-is-turkvision%2C-how-is-the-format-of-turkvision-song-contest-1-h.htm |archivedate=8 March 2016 }}</ref> Unlike the [[Eurovision Song Contest]] in which the winning country proceeds to host the following year's event, hosting of the Turkvision Song Contest takes place in the country or region that is also hosting the [[Culture and Arts Capital of the Turkic World|Turkish Capital of Culture]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Where Will Turkvision Be Held, In Which Country Is Turkvision |url=http://www.turkvision.info/Where-Will-Turkvision-Be-Held,-In-Which-Country-Is-Turkvision-4-h.htm |publisher=turkvision.info |accessdate=22 April 2017 |date=15 October 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311020026/http://turkvision.info/where-will-turkvision-be-held%2C-in-which-country-is-turkvision-4-h.htm |archivedate=11 March 2016 }}</ref>
==History== ===Turkvision Song Contest 2014=== On 25 September 2014 it was confirmed that Albania would make their official debut at the 2014 Song Contest to be held in [[Kazan]], [[Tatarstan]].<ref name=TSC2014>{{cite web|last1=Schneider|first1=Patrick|title=Albania: Turkvision artist presented|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/10/25/albania-turkvizyon-artist-presented/|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=26 October 2014|date=25 October 2014}}</ref> For a short period of time it appeared that Albania had withdrawn from the contest, the official website Turkvizyon.tv removed all mention of Albania from their website.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Albania: Withdraw From Turkvizyon 2014?|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/11/albania-withdraw-from-turkvizyon-2014/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> On 12 November 2014 it was confirmed by Xhoi that she was still participating and that she would be singing "Zjarr Dhe Ajer", the song was later partially translated into Turkish for the contest.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Albania: Still Participating In Turkvizyon?|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/12/albania-still-participating-in-turkvizyon/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=1 March 2015}}</ref> She finished in nineteenth place, achieving a score of 154 points, and therefore failed to qualify for the grand final.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Fidan|first1=Mustafa|title=Turkvizyon 2014: 15 entries qualified for the final|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/20/turkvizyon-2014-15-entries-qualified-for-the-final/|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=20 November 2014|date=20 November 2014}}</ref>
===Turkvision Song Contest 2015=== As the official website published the preliminary participants list for 2015, Albania was not among them, on 7 November 2015 it was confirmed that Albania would participate in the contest for a second year, it was announced that Xhoi Bejko and Visar Rexhepi would represent Albania in Istanbul.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Albania: Will Participate in Turkvizyon 2015|url=http://eurovoix-world.com/albania-will-participate-in-turkvizyon-2015/|website=Eurovoix-World.com|accessdate=18 May 2016}}</ref> Xhoi Bejko and Visar Rexhepi represented Albania at the contest in Istanbul with the song "Adı hasret"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Albania: "Adi Hasret for Turkvizyon 2015"|url=http://eurovoix-world.com/albania-adi-hasret-song-for-turkvizyon-2015/|website=Eurovoix-World.com|accessdate=18 May 2016}}</ref> At the contest, thy finished in eighth place, achieving 154 points.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Kyrgyzstan has won the third Turkvizyon Song Contest|url=http://eurovoix-world.com/turkvizyon15-kyrgyzstan-has-won-the-third-turkvizyon-song-contest/|website=Eurovoix|publisher=eurovoix-world.com|accessdate=19 December 2015|date=19 December 2015}}</ref>
