{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2017}} [[File:Danny Clayton (6465374585).jpg|thumb]] [[File:Danny Clayton (7248271194).jpg|thumb|Danny Clayton attends event at [[The Entertainment Quarter|Fox Studios]]]] '''Danny J. Clayton''' is an Australian Television presenter.<ref>http://www.vmusic.com.au/presenters/danny-clayton.aspx</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.entertainoz.com.au/Celebrities/Television/Danny-Clayton-NSW |title=Danny Clayton :: Television @ EntertainOz |website=www.entertainoz.com.au |access-date=2016-03-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310185631/http://www.entertainoz.com.au/Celebrities/Television/Danny-Clayton-NSW |archivedate=2016-03-10 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.harrymmiller.com.au/2012/05/04/danny-clayton/|title=Danny Clayton {{!}} Harry M Miller|access-date=2016-03-10}}</ref>
== Personal life == Growing up on Sydney's [[Northern Beaches]], Clayton attended [[St Aloysius' College (Sydney)|St Aloysius' College]]. Whilst he was still at school Clayton entered [[Channel V Australia]] 'Snapper' competition, aged 16 years, which he won, giving him the opportunity to work as a photographer with one of Australia's biggest music television channels, shooting music festivals and gigs all around Australia.
After [[Channel V Australia|Channel [V]]] management witnessed Clayton spontaneously storming the stage during filming of an episode of the well known [[Australian Idol]] and entertaining the crowd with his charismatic banter, they decided to trial him as a TV host for the channel.
On the day Clayton graduated{{from where?|date=September 2016}} he was offered a full-time contract to continue his employment at Channel [V] as the youngest VJ on air alongside [[Osher Günsberg|Andrew G]], [[Yumi Stynes]], [[Maya Jupiter]] and [[James Mathison]].{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}
