{{orphan|date=December 2017}}
'''Nuntaa''' (known also as kutkuteh<ref name="news">{{cite web |url=http://justnewsbd.com/details_archive.php?jnewsbd=MTIwNjM= |script-title=মজার খেলা নুনতা |language=Bengali |date=19 September 2012|accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref> in Jessore and Khulna) is a [[Bangladesh]]i game that is played by [[child]]ren and [[teenager]]s in rural areas. It is usually played in groups. In nuntaa, a child stands in a circle, and has to chase the others.<ref name="shaptahik">{{cite web| url=http://www.shaptahik-2000.com/?p=1239 | script-title=বাঙালির খেলা | publisher= shaptahik-2000 |language=Bengali | accessdate=2013-05-22 | author=Z M Saad}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Ahmed |first=Wakil |year=2012 |chapter=Folk Games |chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Folk_Games |editor1-last=Islam |editor1-first=Sirajul |editor1-link=Sirajul Islam |editor2-last=Jamal |editor2-first=Ahmed A. |title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |edition=Second |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]]}}</ref><ref name="kalerkantho">{{cite web | url=http://www.kalerkantho.com/?view=details&feature=yes&type=gold&data=Loan&pub_no=306&cat_id=3&menu_id=83&news_type_id=1&index=11&archiev=yes&arch_date=09-10-2010 | script-title=নুনতা খেলা | work=The Daily Kalerkantho |language=Bengali | date=2 November 2010 | accessdate=2013-05-22| author=মোহাম্মদ আসাদ |location=Dhaka}}</ref>
== System == In nuntaa, a circular area called the "house" is drawn on the ground. One person is then selected as the "nuntaa", and stands outside the house, while the others stay inside the house. The player outside starts reciting "Nuntaa Bolooree"; those inside reply "ek holooree". After saying "Nuntaa" up to seven times, the others run away, and the nuntaa occupies the house.<ref name="bdnews24">{{cite web|url=http://kidz.bdnews24.com/mainStory.php?mainstoryid=20 | script-title=নুনতা | publisher= bdnews24.com |language=Bengali | accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref>
After that, the nuntaa [[apnea|holds his breath]] and, while reciting an agreed-upon phrase, the "nuntaa" chases the others. The first person tagged becomes a member of nuntaa and tries to get the others; the nuntaa group thus quickly becomes crowded. The person who is caught last becomes the owner of the house for the next game.<ref name="bdnews24"/> If the nuntaa breathes while running, the others may catch him and beat him on the back until he or they reach the house.
